Proverbs 16-16 <t><f>ⓨ</f> How much better to get wisdom than <f>ⓩ</f>gold! </t><t>To get understanding is to be chosen rather than <f>ⓐ</f>silver.</t>
Proverbs 16-17 <t>The highway of the upright <f>ⓑ</f>turns aside from evil; </t><t>whoever guards his way preserves his life.</t>
Proverbs 16-18 <t><f>ⓒ</f> Pride goes before destruction, </t><t>and a haughty spirit before a fall.</t>
