Proverbs 16-20 <t>Whoever gives thought to the word <f>[2]</f> <f>ⓕ</f>will discover good, </t><t>and blessed is he <f>ⓖ</f>who trusts in the LORD.</t>
Proverbs 16-21 <t>The wise of heart is called discerning, </t><t>and sweetness of speech <f>ⓗ</f>increases persuasiveness.</t>
Proverbs 16-22 <t>Good sense is <f>ⓘ</f>a fountain of life to him who has it, </t><t>but the instruction of fools is folly.</t>
Proverbs 16-23 <t><f>ⓙ</f> The heart of the wise makes his speech judicious </t><t>and adds persuasiveness to his lips.</t>
Proverbs 16-24 <t><f>ⓚ</f> Gracious words are like <f>ⓛ</f>a honeycomb, </t><t>sweetness to the soul and <f>ⓜ</f>health to the body.</t>
Proverbs 16-25 <t>There is a way that seems right to a man, </t><t>but its end is the way to death. <f>[3]</f></t>
Proverbs 16-26 <t>A worker's appetite works for him; </t><t>his <f>ⓝ</f>mouth urges him on.</t>
